text: Great access point connecting One-North to the Rail Corridor. Well-constructed path that makes it easy to hop onto the relatively peaceful trail for a walk, jog, or cycle. From here, you can walk to Holland Village or Tanglin Halt. Perfect for anyone looking to explore the Rail Corridor from the One-North area.
A very convenient entry to the Greenway (Rail Corridor) for those who come from Biopolis or from Holland Ave.

Although it is very beautiful, there are no street lights, it is very dark at night, and the lights under the bridge will suddenly go out. You have to pay close attention to your steps or go there early.
